


The TRI Function-Like Macro "tri.h"

            The TRI function-like macro has the effect that
                -   the function specified by #0 is called with
                    the arguments specified by any arguments
                    specified after #0 then,
                -   if the call returns a positive value, an
                    error message is sent to the standard error
                    stream and the function containing the macro
                    invocation returns 1. Otherwise,
                -   if the call returned zero,
                    execution continues. Otherwise,
                -   the call returned an negative value,
                    and the function containing the macro
                    invocation returns -1.
